The paper discusses the problem of identifying universal low-dimensional features from high-dimensional data for inference tasks in settings involving learning, which is a central problem in machine learning. The paper also uses information geometry as a tool for analysis, which is a subfield of information theory and has applications in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
